{
  "texts": [
    "By introducing adversarial learning between the generator and the discriminator, GAN avoids the trap of maximizing likelihood.",
    "D works to maximize the likelihood that it correctly distinguishes between reals and fakes by increasing the value of log D(x), while G strives to minimize the likelihood that D will predict that its outputs are fake by minimizing the value of log (1-D (G(z)).",
    "This is a minimax game, as stated by Good fellow.",
    "The GAN formula can be found in equation 1, which also contains its definition.",
    "(1) GminDmaxV(D, G) = Ex ∼ Pdata(x)[loadD(x)] + Ez ∼ pz(z) log(1 -D(G(z)))Fig. 1 Basic GAN architecture Equation 1: Mathematical formula of GAN [2] Where; G stands for Generator, D stands for Discriminator, Pdata(x) = real-world data distribution, P(z) = generator distribution, x = Pdata sample (x),z = a sample taken from P (z), D(x) denotes a discriminator network, G(z) denotes the generator network."
  ]
}